# Speyer Tour v2.0.0 — Cursor IDE Rules

## When to use
Implement SpeyerTour when the user requests an onboarding tour, product walkthrough, or tutorial overlay.

## Setup
```html
<!-- With SUI (recommended) -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/adrianspeyer/speyer-ui@3.3.0/dist/sui-tokens.min.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/adrianspeyer/speyer-ui@3.3.0/dist/sui-components.min.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./src/speyer-tour.css">

<!-- Standalone (zero deps) -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./src/speyer-tour.css">
```

## Pattern
```js
import { SpeyerTour } from './src/speyer-tour.js';

const tour = new SpeyerTour({
  tourId: 'unique-id',
  // Optional: labels for i18n
  // labels: { skip: 'Passer', back: 'Retour', next: 'Suivant', finish: 'Terminer', stepOf: '{current} sur {total}' },
  steps: [
    { target: null,       title: 'Welcome',    content: 'Intro text.' },
    { target: '#element', title: 'Feature',    content: 'Description.', placement: 'right' },
    { target: null,       title: 'All done!',  content: 'Outro text.' },
  ],
  onComplete: ({ tourId }) => console.log('done'),
});
tour.start();
```

## Rules
- target: CSS selector or null (floating step)
- title/content: plain text only (textContent, XSS-safe)
- placement: 'bottom' | 'top' | 'left' | 'right' (auto-flips)
- labels: partial overrides supported (only set what you need)
- SUI CSS must load BEFORE speyer-tour.css
- No hardcoded coordinates — library uses getBoundingClientRect()
